data.content:
Build and all 3 tests pass. Here's the fix:

In MSTest 4.x, `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()` now **returns `T`** directly instead of using an `out` parameter. Change:

```csharp
// Old (MSTest 3.x)
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor, out var typed);

// New (MSTest 4.x)
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor);
```

The same pattern applies to all three call sites. The assertion still validates the type and fails the test if incorrect, but the typed value is returned instead of passed via `out`.
